    <div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='3592#1183652061'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2007-07-05T16:14:21+00:00">Jul 5, 2007 04:14 PM UTC</time> by <b>Rob Quick</b><a class="anchor" name="1183652061">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>This should not be a ticket. Closing.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='3592#1181333782'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2007-06-08T20:16:22+00:00">Jun 8, 2007 08:16 PM UTC</time> by <b>OSG-GOC</b><a class="anchor" name="1181333782">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Begin forwarded message&#58;

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; From&#58; Doug Olson &#60;dlolson@....&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Date&#58; June 7, 2007 7&#58;28&#58;57 PM EDT</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; To&#58; Chris Green &#60;greenc@....&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Cc&#58; helm@...., helm@...., Grid Operations Center</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; &#60;goc@....&#62;, Don Petravick &#60;petravick@....&#62;, Ruth</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Pordes &#60;ruth@....&#62;, Keith Chadwick &#60;chadwick@....&#62;,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; dlolson@....</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Subject&#58; Re&#58; [info-doegrids] Need personal robot certs</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; On 6/7/2007 3&#58;44 PM, Chris Green wrote&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; Hi,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; Thanks for all your input on this. For me personally, the workaround</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; is to use the kerberos facility; however many of the people at</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; whom my</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; test script is named will only have access to the DOEGrids CA. I</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; believe this is definitely an idea whose time has come&#58; the use cases</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; are there, the desire for a secure solution is there; and one</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; needs to</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; fill the vacuum before less savory workarounds are found by</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; individuals and the enforcement arm has to kick into gear.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; I don&#39;t know quite what is meant by &#34;proxy&#34; here. That word is</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; overloaded and has many shades of meaning. I need some safe, secure</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; and acceptable method of having&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; In this discussion when I saw proxy, I mean RFC 3820; the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; credential you</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; get from</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; doing grid-proxy-init, voms-proxy-init, myproxy-init, myproxy-</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; logon, etc.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; voms-proxy-init &#60;blah&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<div id='show_469497685' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_469497685'><font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; in a script without having to be physically there at execution</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; time to</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; type a password, punch in a number or prick my finger. I understand</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; that myproxy, unless also running with kerberos, allows a simple</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; password; while this solution is available now, I don&#39;t really</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; want to</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; be encouraging people to use it to then have to swap to safer (but</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; possibly more onerous) methods later.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; You (or the service you specify) can renew proxy credentials from a</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; myproxy server</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; without using a password.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; <a href='http&#58;//grid.ncsa.uiuc.edu/myproxy/renew.html' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>http&#58;//grid.ncsa.uiuc.edu/myproxy/renew.html</a></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; While I personally don&#39;t mind renewing some credential manually once</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; per week, one has to allow some mechanism for delegation to another</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; person otherwise one family emergency could mean essential things</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; don&#39;t get done.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; As I think either Mike or Doug said&#58; my use case here isn&#39;t exactly a</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; &#34;service,&#34; like backup to a grid-based storage resource; a VO manager</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; or other responsible would be</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; gathering information about multiple sites that nominally support</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; that</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; VO and compiling that information from VORS, ReSS/BDII, fork jobs and</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; batch jobs to those sites. This is really an automated user/client</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; operation, not a service. In these days of increased automation</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; across</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; the board, I think it is reasonable to expect and allow a person or</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; organization (with particular safeguards in place) to have scripts</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; run</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; unattended that operate on behalf of that person or organization.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; I think what you describe is a service, which is performing a bunch of</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; client-like actions</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; on behalf of someone.  The current DOEGrids OU=Service certificates</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; can</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; be (and are being)</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; used that way, with the primary restriction that the long lived</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; credential is stored on one machine</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; (whose name is encoded in the cert) so the voms-proxy-init must always</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; be issued</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; from that machine.  It seems to me that covers your case, and is</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; simpler</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; than using myproxy renewal.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; I&#39;m hoping to get this discussed in other fora too, with the aim of</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; getting momentum up towards a solution sooner rather than later.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; The concept of having a long term client service credential which can</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; wonder around</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; and be used from many places without a human touch needs work, I think</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; on both</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; the policy and technical side, to become a reality.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Doug</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; Thanks again for your help and time,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; Chris.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
