<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Hi,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Thanks for all your input on this. For me personally, the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; workaround is to use the kerberos facility; however many of the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; people at whom my test script is named will only have access to the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; DOEGrids CA. I believe this is definitely an idea whose time has</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; come&#58; the use cases are there, the desire for a secure solution is</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; there; and one needs to fill the vacuum before less savory</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; workarounds are found by individuals and the enforcement arm has to</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; kick into gear.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; I don&#39;t know quite what is meant by &#34;proxy&#34; here. That word is</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; overloaded and has many shades of meaning. I need some safe, secure</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; and acceptable method of having&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; voms-proxy-init &#60;blah&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; in a script without having to be physically there at execution time</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; to type a password, punch in a number or prick my finger. I</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; understand that myproxy, unless also running with kerberos, allows</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; a simple password; while this solution is available now, I don&#39;t</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; really want to be encouraging people to use it to then have to swap</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; to safer (but possibly more onerous) methods later. While I</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; personally don&#39;t mind renewing some credential manually once per</font>
<div id='show_516514884' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_516514884'><font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; week, one has to allow some mechanism for delegation to another</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; person otherwise one family emergency could mean essential things</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; don&#39;t get done.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; As I think either Mike or Doug said&#58; my use case here isn&#39;t exactly</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; a &#34;service,&#34; like backup to a grid-based storage resource; a VO</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; manager or other responsible would be</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; gathering information about multiple sites that nominally support</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; that VO and compiling that information from VORS, ReSS/BDII, fork</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; jobs and batch jobs to those sites. This is really an automated</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; user/client operation, not a service. In these days of increased</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; automation across the board, I think it is reasonable to expect and</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; allow a person or organization (with particular safeguards in</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; place) to have scripts run unattended that operate on behalf of</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; that person or organization.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; I&#39;m hoping to get this discussed in other fora too, with the aim of</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; getting momentum up towards a solution sooner rather than later.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Thanks again for your help and time,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Chris.</font>
